  <h2>Application Screens</h2>

  <h3>Screen 1 — Headline Generator (Main Demo)</h3>
  <p>The primary interface. The left panel accepts pasted article text. The right panel presents an author selector dropdown showing each author's article count with a visual label (e.g., "Rich: 127 articles" or "Sparse: 8 articles — Cold-Start Active"). Upon generation, three headline variants are displayed side by side: the non-personalized baseline, vanilla StyleVector, and CS-StyleVector. A radar chart shows which style dimensions each generated headline activates relative to the author's known style vector.</p>

  <h3>Screen 2 — Author Explorer</h3>
  <p>A grid of author cards showing profile metadata. Clicking an author shows their style cluster membership, the top 5 most style-representative tokens from their historical headlines, and their position in a t-SNE visualization of the style vector space. Sparse authors show their interpolated vector position alongside the cluster centroid that contributed to it.</p>

  <h3>Screen 3 — Research Results Dashboard</h3>
  <p>A static page presenting the evaluation results — ROUGE-L, METEOR, and BERTScore tables across all four methods for both rich and sparse author groups. Bar charts comparing method performance. The alpha sweep chart for cold-start. This page serves as the "paper" section of the application and is the primary resource for the chalk talk.</p>

  <h2>Key API Endpoints</h2>
  <pre><span class="cm"># api/main.py</span>

<span class="cm"># POST /generate</span>
<span class="cm"># Body: { article: str, author_id: str, methods: ["baseline","stylevec","coldstart"] }</span>
<span class="cm"># Returns: { headlines: {...}, style_similarity: float, cluster_id: int }</span>

<span class="cm"># GET /authors</span>
<span class="cm"># Returns: list of authors with article_count, cluster_id, is_sparse flags</span>

<span class="cm"># GET /results</span>
<span class="cm"># Returns: pre-computed evaluation table (static, loaded from JSON)</span>

<span class="cm"># GET /health</span>
<span class="cm"># Returns: { status: "ok", model: "llama-2-7b", vectors_loaded: int }</span></pre>

  <div class="callout">
    <div class="callout-label">Important Deployment Note</div>
    <p>The deployed application does NOT run LLaMA-2-7B locally. All heavy model inference calls go through the HuggingFace Inference API. Style vectors are pre-computed during training and stored as .npy files loaded at server startup. This makes the Docker container lightweight (~500MB) and keeps HuggingFace Spaces within free-tier compute limits.</p>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- SECTION 10: CI/CD PIPELINE -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="section">
  <h1><span class="sec-num">§10</span> CI/CD Pipeline</h1>

  <p>The CI/CD pipeline is implemented via GitHub Actions with two workflow files. It is initialized from Day 1 of the project — not added at the end.</p>

  <h2>Workflow 1 — Continuous Integration (ci.yml)</h2>
  <p>Triggered on every push and pull request to any branch. Runs automated tests on the backend API, data pipeline utilities, and the cold-start interpolation module. A failing test blocks the PR from being merged.</p>

  <pre><span class="cm"># .github/workflows/ci.yml</span>
<span class="var">name</span>: CI
<span class="var">on</span>: [push, pull_request]

<span class="var">jobs</span>:
  <span class="var">test</span>:
    <span class="var">runs-on</span>: ubuntu-latest
    <span class="var">steps</span>:
      - <span class="var">uses</span>: actions/checkout@v3
      - <span class="var">name</span>: Set up Python 3.10
        <span class="var">uses</span>: actions/setup-python@v4
        <span class="var">with</span>: { python-version: '<span class="num">3.10</span>' }
      - <span class="var">name</span>: Install dependencies
        <span class="var">run</span>: pip install -r requirements.txt
      - <span class="var">name</span>: Run unit tests
        <span class="var">run</span>: pytest tests/ -v --tb=short
      - <span class="var">name</span>: Lint check
        <span class="var">run</span>: ruff check src/</pre>

  <h2>Workflow 2 — Continuous Deployment (deploy.yml)</h2>
  <p>Triggered only when code is merged into the <code>main</code> branch. Builds the Docker container and pushes to HuggingFace Spaces. Simultaneously, Vercel auto-deploys the frontend from the same repository through its GitHub integration (no additional workflow needed for frontend).</p>

  <pre><span class="cm"># .github/workflows/deploy.yml</span>
<span class="var">name</span>: Deploy to HuggingFace Spaces
<span class="var">on</span>:
  <span class="var">push</span>:
    <span class="var">branches</span>: [main]

<span class="var">jobs</span>:
  <span class="var">deploy</span>:
    <span class="var">runs-on</span>: ubuntu-latest
    <span class="var">steps</span>:
      - <span class="var">uses</span>: actions/checkout@v3
        <span class="var">with</span>: { fetch-depth: <span class="num">0</span> }
      - <span class="var">name</span>: Push backend to HuggingFace Spaces
        <span class="var">env</span>:
          HF_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.HF_TOKEN }}
        <span class="var">run</span>: |
          git config user.email "ci@project.com"
          git config user.name "CI Bot"
          git remote add hf https://user:$HF_TOKEN@huggingface.co/spaces/USERNAME/cs-stylevector
          git subtree push --prefix=. hf main</pre>

  <h2>Dockerfile</h2>
  <pre><span class="cm"># docker/Dockerfile</span>
<span class="kw">FROM</span> python:<span class="num">3.10</span>-slim

<span class="kw">WORKDIR</span> /app
<span class="kw">COPY</span> requirements.txt .
<span class="kw">RUN</span> pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

<span class="kw">COPY</span> src/api/ ./api/
<span class="kw">COPY</span> vectors/ ./vectors/       <span class="cm"># pre-computed style vectors</span>
<span class="kw">COPY</span> data/author_registry.json .

<span class="kw">EXPOSE</span> <span class="num">7860</span>   <span class="cm"># HuggingFace Spaces default port</span>
<span class="kw">CMD</span> [<span class="st">"uvicorn"</span>, <span class="st">"api.main:app"</span>, <span class="st">"--host"</span>, <span class="st">"0.0.0.0"</span>, <span class="st">"--port"</span>, <span class="st">"7860"</span>]</pre>

  <h2>Test Coverage Plan</h2>
  <p>The test suite covers the following critical paths: agnostic headline generation (mock API call, verify output format), activation extraction (check tensor shapes and dtype), style vector computation (verify mean difference formula, normalize output), cold-start interpolation (verify α=0 returns sparse vector, α=1 returns centroid, intermediate values interpolate correctly), and all API endpoints (status codes, response schema validation).</p>
</div>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- SECTION 11: TIMELINE -->
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="section">
  <h1><span class="sec-num">§11</span> Implementation Timeline</h1>

  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="tl-row">
      <div class="tl-week">Week 1</div>
      <div class="tl-spine"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-line"></div></div>
